'''Sipho Justin Chaine''' (born 14 December 1996) is a South African [[association football|soccer]] player who plays as a goalkeeper for [[Orlando Pirates F.C.|Orlando Pirates]] in the [[South African Premier Division]]. He is recognized as one of the best goalkeepers in the Betway Premiership and also represents the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]].

He was selected as the [[2024–25 South African Premiership]] goalkeeper of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kappel |first=David |date=2025-07-29 |title=All 24/25 PSL Awards Winners Revealed |url=https://www.idiskitimes.co.za/local/all-24-25-psl-awards-winners-revealed/ |access-date=2025-07-30 |website=iDiski Times |language=en-US}}</ref>

==Club career==
Chaine played for [[Bloemfontein Celtic F.C.|Bloemfontein Celtic]], among others in the [[Diski Challenge Shield]], and was drafted into the senior team.<ref name=celtic>{{cite news|url=https://www.iol.co.za/sport/soccer/psl/sipho-chaine-credits-support-and-mentality-for-settling-in-quickly-at-orlando-pirates-a4cc78d8-5056-4d7c-81d6-a376fe44464c|title=Sipho Chaine credits support and mentality for settling in quickly at Orlando Pirates|date=15 March 2023|author=Baleka, Mihlali|publisher=IOL|access-date=26 July 2024}}</ref> He made his first-tier debut in May 2019 in a 3-1 win against AmaZulu FC, in what would be his only appearance for the season.<ref>{{Soccerway|sipho-chaine/454464|access-date=26 July 2024}}</ref> He would get more minutes in the 2020/2021 season, where he made a total of 15 appearances across all competitions for Bloemfontein Celtic. When [[Royal AM F.C.|Royal AM]] bought the status of Bloemfontein Celtic, Chaine continued in that team, but barely saw any playing time.<ref name=celtic/>

In the summer of 2022, Chaine signed for [[Chippa United F.C.|Chippa United]]. After only two appearances for Chippa United, Chaine was signed in September 2022, on the last day of the transfer window, by major club [[Orlando Pirates F.C.|Orlando Pirates]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.idiskitimes.co.za/featured/confirmed-pirates-complete-2nd-deadline-day-signing/|title=Confirmed: Pirates Complete 2nd Deadline Day Signing|date=22 September 2022|author=|publisher=iDiski Times|access-date=26 July 2024}}</ref>

He started as a third choice behind [[Richard Ofori (goalkeeper)|Richard Ofori]] and [[Siyabonga Mpontshane]], but after the 2022 World Cup break, Chaine was finally able to start his first match for Orlando Pirates. He remained the first choice throughout the season, including the Pirates' victory in the [[2022–23 Nedbank Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.idiskitimes.co.za/nedbank-cup/chaine-pinching-himself-at-pirates-trophy-success/|title=Chaine Pinching Himself At Pirates' Trophy Success|date=4 June 2023|author=Madlala, Robin-Duke|publisher=iDiski Times|access-date=26 July 2024}}</ref> At the same time, some claimed that Chaine kept too few clean sheets.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/news/orlando-pirates-goalkeeping-ofori-start-chaine-in-soweto-derby-five-clean-sheets-in-17-matches/blt589c43a192d45e0d|title=Orlando Pirates goalkeeping issue: Should Ofori start ahead of Chaine in Soweto Derby with only five clean sheets in 17 matches?|date=4 May 2023|author=Ditlhobolo, Austin|publisher=Goal|access-date=26 July 2024}}</ref>

In the 2023–24 season, Chaine emerged as the first-choice goalkeeper, dislodging [[Richard Ofori (goalkeeper)|Richard Ofori]] in the process. His heroics in the penalty shootout against Mamelodi Sundowns helped the team win the [[2023 MTN 8]] in October 2023.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.news24.com/sport/soccer/psl/orlando-pirates-retain-mtn8-crown-through-sipho-chaines-gifted-hands-20231007|title= Orlando Pirates retain MTN8 crown through Sipho Chaine's gifted hands|date=7 October 2023|author=Ngidi, Njabulo|publisher=News 24|access-date=26 July 2024}}</ref> At the same time, he was injured in the MTN 8 final, and was kept out of playing until February 2024.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://supersport.com/football/dstv-premiership/news/83796732-01b4-4ebe-bf55-d43e4c029961/chaine-back-from-injury-for-buccaneers|title=Chaine back from injury for Buccaneers|date=29 December 2023|author=|publisher=Super Sport|access-date=26 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/sipho-chaine-orlando-pirates-provide-latest-injury-update-on-goalkeeper-ahead-of-crunch-mamelodi-sundowns-tie/blta515eabaddb6f603#cse996d1ce54e34ce8|title=Sipho Chaine: Orlando Pirates provide latest injury update on goalkeeper ahead of crunch Mamelodi Sundowns tie|date=16 February 2024|author=Madyira, Michael|publisher=16 February 2024|access-date=26 July 2024}}</ref> Returning from injury, Chaine helped win the [[2023–24 Nedbank Cup]]. At a crucial moment in the cup final, Chaine saved a penalty from [[Lucas Ribeiro Costa]] in the early minutes of the game.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.idiskitimes.co.za/nedbank-cup/pirates-complete-cup-double-win-over-sundowns-with-nedbank-cup-title/|title=Pirates Complete Cup Double Win Over Sundowns With Nedbank Cup Title|date=1 June 2024|author=|publisher=iDiski Times|access-date=26 July 2024}}</ref>

In May 2024, a video was released in which Chaine said he would bet on an English soccer match; soccer betting is prohibited for any soccer player. Chaine and Orlando Pirates stated that the video was made in jest.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.sowetanlive.co.za/sport/2024-05-15-bucs-chaine-in-hot-water-after-viral-betting-video/|title=Bucs' Chaine in hot water after viral 'betting' video|date=15 May 2024|author=Ndebele, Sihle|publisher=The Sowetan|access-date=26 July 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Chaine's stellar performances for Orlando Pirates earned him a call up to the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]]. He made his debut  on 10 September 2024 in an [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualification Group K|Africa Cup of Nations qualifier]] against South Sudan at the [[Juba Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2024/09/10/africa/africa-cup-of-nations-qualification/south-sudan/south-africa/4406443/|title=South Sudan v South Africa game report|date=10 September 2024}}</ref>

On 1 December 2025, Chaine was called up to the South Africa squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/totalenergies-afcon-morocco-2025-fever-rises-as-broos-become-first-coach-to-unveil-final-squad/|title=TotalEnergies AFCON Morocco 2025 fever rises as Broos become first coach to unveil final squad|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=1 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

